⎩112⎭
  function code (name, flags, does) {⎩113⎭
      ⌈ Add new word to RAM dictionary. We create a word (Forth "object") in RAM with 5 fields and extend the⎩114⎭
	the dictionary by linking back to the head of the dictionary list ⌉⎩115⎭
      x ⇐ λlen (State.RAM)⎩116⎭
⎩117⎭
      %ram+ (State.LAST) ⌈ (LFA) link to previous word in dictionary list ⌉⎩118⎭
      %ram+ (name)       ⌈ (NFA) name of word ⌉⎩119⎭
      %ram+ (flags)      ⌈       0 = normal word, 1 = immediate word ⌉⎩120⎭
      %ram+ (does)       ⌈ (CFA) function pointer that points to code that executes the word (a function pointer is now just a string (probably should be optimized to be a bytecode)) ⌉⎩121⎭
⎩122⎭
      State.LAST ⇐ x                ⌈ LAST is the pointer to the head of the dictionary list, set it to point to⎩123⎭
					this new word ⌉⎩124⎭
  }⎩125⎭
⎩126⎭
  function literalize () {⎩127⎭
      ⌈ Compile literal into definition. ⌉⎩128⎭
      %ram+ (λ_find ("(literal)"))  ⌈# Compile address of doliteral. ⌉⎩129⎭
      %ram+ (%pop)             ⌈ # Compile literal value. ⌉⎩130⎭
  }⎩131⎭
⎩132⎭
