⎩368⎭
  ⌈ Example of state-smart word, which Brodie sez not to do. Sorry, Leo... ⌉⎩369⎭
  ⌈ This sin allows it to be used the same way compiling or interactive. ⌉⎩370⎭
  subr ' {⎩371⎭
      ⌈ ( -- string) Read up to closing dquote, push to stack ⌉⎩372⎭
      ⌈ A string in Forth begins with the word " (followed by a space) then all characters up to the next " ⌉⎩373⎭
